            <h4>What is the current population of Minneapolis?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Minneapolis is 1,948.  Minneapolis, Kansas is the 7,715th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Minneapolis?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Minneapolis was in
                    2000, when its population was
                    2,055.
                    
                        In 2000, Minneapolis was the
                        7,271st largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 7,715th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Minneapolis is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            5.2%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 2000.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Minneapolis shrinking?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Minneapolis has shrunk
                        5.2% 
                        since the year 2000.
                    


                    
                        Minneapolis, Kansas's growth is below average.
                        71% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
